    "updated_at": "2017-06-08T05:35:20Z",
    "body": "Following code works for me.\r\n```js\r\n...\r\nimport demo from './demo.html'\r\n\r\nclass WVCheck extends React.Component{\r\n  render(){\r\n    return (\r\n      <View style={{ height:700 }}>\r\n        <WebView\r\n\t  source = { webapp }\r\n\t  style={{borderColor:'green',borderWidth:400,width:300,height:1200}}/>\r\n      </View>\r\n    )\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich is interesting,the `WebView` component will not fill it's parent `View` element,it means that you have to offer height to parent `View` element"
